text: John Marshall (fl. 1384–1392), of Cambridge, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Cambridge in April 1384 and September 1388. He was mayor of Cambridge from September 1391 to 1392. ==References== Category:Year of birth missing Category:Year of death missing Category:English MPs April 1384 Category:People from Cambridge Category:Mayors of Cambridge Category:English MPs September 1388
